  "response_text": "**Technical Manual for Prosthetic Limb**\n\n**Introduction**\nWelcome to the user manual for your new prosthetic limb. This manual is designed not only to guide you through the technical aspects of your device but also to acknowledge and support your emotional journey as you adapt to your new limb. We understand that adjusting to a prosthetic can be challenging, and we are here to support you every step of the way.\n\n**1. Technical Specifications**\n- **Material:** The prosthetic limb is made from a combination of lightweight carbon fiber and advanced polymers for durability and comfort.\n- **Control System:** Equipped with a myoelectric control system that allows for natural movement and fine motor skills.\n- **Battery Life:** The battery provides up to 8 hours of continuous use on a single charge.\n- **Maintenance:** Regular cleaning and inspection are recommended to ensure optimal performance.\n\n**2. Setup and Initial Use**\n- **Initial Fitting:** Your prosthetic will be custom fitted to ensure a comfortable and secure fit. Follow all instructions provided by your healthcare provider.\n- **Wearing Instructions:** Start by wearing the prosthetic for short periods, gradually increasing the duration as you become more comfortable.\n- **Adjustments:** Regular adjustments may be necessary to maintain proper fit and function. Consult your healthcare provider if you notice any discomfort or changes in fit.\n\n**3. Emotional Support**\n- **Understanding Your Feelings:** It's normal to experience a range of emotions as you adjust to your new limb. Feelings of sadness, anger, or frustration are common and should be acknowledged.\n- **Support Network:** Reach out to friends, family, or support groups who can offer emotional support during this transition.\n- **Professional Help:** If you find it difficult to cope, consider speaking with a counselor or therapist who specializes in prosthetic adaptation.\n\n**4. Troubleshooting Common Issues**\n- **Discomfort or Pain:** Adjust the fit of the prosthetic or consult your healthcare provider.\n- **Movement Issues:** Check the battery level and ensure the control system is functioning correctly.\n- **Skin Irritation:** Apply a barrier cream to prevent skin irritation and consult your healthcare provider if the issue persists.\n\n**5. Advanced Features**\n- **Customization Options:** You can customize the appearance and functionality of your prosthetic to better suit your needs and preferences.\n- **Integration with Assistive Technologies:** Explore how your prosthetic can integrate with other assistive technologies to enhance your daily life.\n\n**6. Maintenance and Care**\n- **Cleaning:** Clean the prosthetic regularly using mild soap and water.\n- **Storage:** Store the prosthetic in a cool, dry place when not in use.\n- **Replacement Parts:** Keep track of any replacement parts needed for maintenance and contact your healthcare provider for assistance.\n\n**7. Contact Information**\nFor further assistance, please contact our customer service team at [contact information].\n\n---\n\n**Acknowledgment of Emotional Experience**\nWe recognize that adapting to a prosthetic limb is a significant life",
